			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			After reading the Honor thread, I had a brain fut.  Dunno if that's good or not. :b  Anyway..<br />
<br />
1)  As honor goes up, would it be possible for Diplomacy to go up as well?  Not the 2 points per day, but possibly 1 point for every 10-15 honor points?  This could also work in reverse; honor losses affect one's Diplomacy stat.  As for attacks on the Empire, it could lower one's Diplomacy a lot.  I'm not sure if this would be &quot;useful,&quot; but maybe y'all can throw out some ideas yay-or-nay.<br />
<br />
2)  Pretty please with chocolate syrup (and whipped cream and cherry on top) could there be a way to keep the commander views constant?<br />
<br />
3)  How about a check-all box for fleets on the defense/attack pages?<br />
<br />
4)  When recalling a fleet from stationing, it shows a list of the recalled fleets before pressing [OK].  Could it be possible to have that kind of thing on the train page so you can be sure that the fleets you're sending are really fleets that you WANT to send?  I know how much it takes to train a certain size ship, but maybe n00bs don't?  I dunno.<br />
<br />
'kay, looking those over, they sound like a bunch of &quot;lazy person&quot; suggestions.  ^^;  Anybody got anything to say about these?<br />
<br />
Rosey &lt;3						<P align=right> </P>
